### pickNode() {#a25dcd4c29d28fbdc0d457e7da5e6ee75}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>SUnit &#42; anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;GCNIterativeScheduler.cpp&#125;::SchedStrategyStub::pickNode (bool &amp; IsTopNode)</>}
  labels = {["inline", "virtual"]}>
Pick the next node to schedule, or return NULL.

Set IsTopNode to true to schedule the node at the top of the unscheduled region. Otherwise it will be scheduled at the bottom.

### shouldTrackLaneMasks() {#a714e2456d7b9d278c7bf71fbf0a29a24}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;GCNIterativeScheduler.cpp&#125;::SchedStrategyStub::shouldTrackLaneMasks () const</>}
  labels = {["inline", "virtual"]}>
Returns true if lanemasks should be tracked.

LaneMask tracking is necessary to reorder independent subregister defs for the same vreg. This has to be enabled in combination with <a href="#a376803a4832fd696122afd9f644e862b">shouldTrackPressure()</a>.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/gcniterativescheduler-cpp/#l00207">207</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/gcniterativescheduler-cpp">GCNIterativeScheduler.cpp</a>.
